                             \"IsEnabled\": null\n                            }\n                          ],\n                          \"CalibrationType\": 4,\n                          \"Description\": \"<p><span style=\\\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\\\">The page provides a proposed set of rules and processes for implementing SB 102 (2023), inclusive of the recent legislative changes made by SB 328 (2024), known as the \\u201cLive Local Act\\u201d (\\u201cAct\\u201d).&nbsp;</span><strong style=\\\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\\\">Please check back often as these guidelines will be refined as we work through the initial round of Live Local Act projects.&nbsp;</strong><span style=\\\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\\\">Where words are capitalized, it generally indicates a defined term in Miami 21.</span></p><ul><li>The highest density allowed in the jurisdiction, which is 1000 dwelling units per acre;</li><li>The height permitted within 1 mile \\u201cfor a commercial or residential development\\u201d (unless restricted due to adjacency to a T3 Transect Zone);</li><li>If located in a zone without multifamily use, such use is permitted by right, unless T3; and</li><li>An FLR of 36.</li></ul>\",\n                          \"GridicsId\": null,\n                          \"Id\": 79686,\n                          \"Name\": \"Live Local (SB 102) - Applicable\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                          \"Attributes\": [],\n                          \"CalibrationType\": 4,\n                          \"Description\": \"<p>Shall be provided for all T4, T5, T6, CS, CI, CI-HD, and D zones, as shown in Article 4, Table 4, Miami21.</p>\",\n                          \"GridicsId\": null,\n                          \"Id\": 40019,\n                          \"Name\": \"Off-street bicycle parking\"\n                        }\n                      ],\n                      \"Uses\": [\n                        {\n                          \"AllowedUsesDescription